 \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 720, \"end\": 734, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Antichrist\", \"score\": 0.9999989871444668, \"rank\": 1.0128567514101717e-06, \"text\": \"anti-Christian\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Antichrist\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Antichrist\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"From scenes that appeared satanic to moments that could have come straight from The Book of Revelation in the Bible, the creators laughingly claimed the symbols were just rock music, volcanoes, the \\\"Olympic Spirit\\\" or wings of a dove.\", \"from\": 745, \"to\": 979, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"However, when put all together and added to the outright mockery of Christianity in a disgusting portrayal of The Last Supper with a female DJ Jesus, their excuses were not believable in the least.\", \"from\": 980, \"to\": 1177, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1048, \"end\": 1060, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Christianity\", \"score\": 0.999999999829015, \"rank\": 1.7111847020046844e-10, \"text\": \"Christianity\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Christianity\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Christianity\"}, {\"begin\": 1123, \"end\": 1128, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Jesus\", \"score\": 0.9999999999872671, \"rank\": 1.2417892815109204e-11, \"text\": \"Jesus\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Jesus\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Jesus\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Near the beginning, a man with angel wings plays the accordion on a bridge above the Seine River where the ceremony took place, already hinting at a Christian theme.\", \"from\": 1179, \"to\": 1344, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1328, \"end\": 1337, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Christianity\", \"score\": 0.9999997539917179, \"rank\": 2.460075966275219e-07, \"text\": \"Christian\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Christianity\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Christianity\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The satanic imagery started during a rock segment as a creepy decapitated Marie Antoinette appears in several windows and chants while a hellish atmosphere with pitchforks, fire, and red colors flash by:                Kelly: What?\", \"from\": 1360, \"to\": 1591, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1434, \"end\": 1450, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Marie_Antoinette\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 1.75840914833389e-41, \"text\": \"Marie Antoinette\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Marie_Antoinette\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Marie_Antoinette\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Can we talk about all the different styles of music and dancing?\", \"from\": 1592, \"to\": 1656, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"This is incredible.\", \"from\": 1657, \"to\": 1676, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Michael: You mean we do not mix \\\"Les Miz\\\" with heavy metal every day?\", \"from\": 1678, \"to\": 1747, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Kelly: Yes, we do.\", \"from\": 1749, \"to\": 1767, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Incredible.\", \"from\": 1768, \"to\": 1779, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Oh my gosh.\", \"from\": 1780, \"to\": 1791, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"We just had metal after \\\"Les Miz,\\\" after can-can.\", \"from\": 1792, \"to\": 1841, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Michael: And that image representing Marie Antoinette, and this section is called Liberty, exploring the Paris political emancipation over time.\", \"from\": 1843, \"to\": 1987, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1880, \"end\": 1896, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Marie_Antoinette\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 1.75840914833389e-41, \"text\": \"Marie Antoinette\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Marie_Antoinette\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Marie_Antoinette\"}, {\"begin\": 1925, \"end\": 1932, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Liberty\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 3.109535654176264e-16, \"text\": \"Liberty\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Liberty\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Liberty\"}, {\"begin\": 1948, \"end\": 1953, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 3.479270854497296e-23, \"text\": \"Paris\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Oh, okay.\", \"from\": 1989, \"to\": 1998, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"It's just rock and roll and freedom.\", \"from\": 1999, \"to\": 2035, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Gotcha.\", \"from\": 2036, \"to\": 2043, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"During a segment featuring a m\\u00e9nage \\u00e0 trois, the three lovers are first seen in a library reading books.\", \"from\": 2045, \"to\": 2149, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2074, \"end\": 2088, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Threesome\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 4.712517180152534e-50, \"text\": \"m\\u00e9nage \\u00e0 trois\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Threesome\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Threesome\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"As they pull various tomes from the shelves the camera focuses on the titles.\", \"from\": 2150, \"to\": 2227, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"One book, 'Le Diable Au Corps,' which translates to \\\"The Devil in the Body,\\\" is about a 16-year-old child who has an affair with a married woman who is fifteen years older than her while her husband is at war.\", \"from\": 2228, \"to\": 2437, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"The creators were not sly about their true messaging when it came to a runway/fashion show segment on a foot bridge during the \\\"Festive\\\" section of the show, as a group that included drag queens, a female Jesus DJ, and a child (who later walks the runway, as well), portrayed The Last Supper at the opening:                Michael: Look at Snoop's reaction when he heard that.\", \"from\": 2439, \"to\": 2815, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2644, \"end\": 2649, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Jesus\", \"score\": 0.9999999999872671, \"rank\": 1.2417892815109204e-11, \"text\": \"Jesus\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Jesus\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Jesus\"}, {\"begin\": 2650, \"end\": 2652, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Disc_jockey\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 3.834234282748857e-18, \"text\": \"DJ\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Disc_jockey\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Disc_jockey\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"He's visiting with us from up on that perch at the Plaza de la Concorde.\", \"from\": 2816, \"to\": 2888, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"This is the bridge very close to the Eiffel Tower.If we talk about food, we talk about music, we also talk about fashion.\", \"from\": 2889, \"to\": 3010, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"So many of those things, so ingrained in French culture.\", \"from\": 3011, \"to\": 3067, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 3052, \"end\": 3066, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Culture_of_France\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"French culture\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Culture_of_France\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Culture_of_France\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Little bit of a party time now.\", \"from\": 3068, \"to\": 3099, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Kelly: Yeah!\", \"from\": 3101, \"to\": 3113, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Michael: We saw a red carpet earlier.\", \"from\": 3115, \"to\": 3152, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"When you think of red carpets around the world, nothing matches the red carpet in Paris.\", \"from\": 3153, \"to\": 3241, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 3235, \"end\": 3240, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 3.479270854497296e-23, \"text\": \"Paris\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The fashion show in France in the spring brings the beautiful people from around the world.\", \"from\": 3242, \"to\": 3333, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 3262, \"end\": 3268, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\", \"score\": 0.9999726700613193, \"rank\": 2.2411906689668545e-05, \"text\": \"France\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Every designer comes here, so you knew, Kelly, in the opening ceremony,the tribute to the fashion show.\", \"from\": 3334, \"to\": 3437, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Kelly: And on the bridge?This is incredibly cool.\", \"from\": 3439, \"to\": 3488, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"And that is a wet floor.\", \"from\": 3489, \"to\": 3513, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Do not slip.\", \"from\": 3514, \"to\": 3526, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"That was going to be my\\u00a0outfit, but I heard she was\\u00a0going to wear it, so I was like,\\u00a0okay.\", \"from\": 3527, \"to\": 3617, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Michael: I am looking.\", \"from\": 3619, \"to\": 3641, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"This is a footbridge.\", \"from\": 3642, \"to\": 3663, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"This is a bridge that people\\u00a0traverse all the time, and what\\u00a0they did to all the monuments\\u00a0and all the places in Paris to\\u00a0bring it alive as a stage above\\u00a0the Seine.\", \"from\": 3664, \"to\": 3828, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 3777, \"end\": 3782, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 3.479270854497296e-23, \"text\": \"Paris\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\"}, {\"begin\": 3822, \"end\": 3827, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Seine\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 4.650926879912855e-24, \"text\": \"Seine\", \"types\": [\"Q47521\", \"Q4022\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Seine\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Seine\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Peyton Manning: It's just not normal to turn\\u00a0a bridge into a runway walk.There is a great documentary on Peacock about the creation of\\u00a0the show.\", \"from\": 3830, \"to\": 3974, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"It shows how many people were\\u00a0involved in this ceremony.\", \"from\": 3975, \"to\": 4031, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"It's pretty stunning.The rain has probably forced them\\u00a0to audible a little bit, and you\\u00a0know, the fact that they had to\\u00a0keep so many things secret.\", \"from\": 4032, \"to\": 4179, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Kelly was talking about how hard\\u00a0it is to perform live when there\\u00a0was no rehearsal.\", \"from\": 4180, \"to\": 4263, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 4180, \"end\": 4185, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Kelly_Osbourne\", \"score\": 0.9989247090021358, \"rank\": 0.0010764484935629388, \"text\": \"Kelly\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Kelly_Osbourne\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Kelly_Osbourne\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"It was no, like I said, live\\u00a0reps.It's incredible what Paris and\\u00a0this entire opening ceremony is\\u00a0pulling off.\", \"from\": 4264, \"to\": 4373, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 4319, \"end\": 4324, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 3.479270854497296e-23, \"text\": \"Paris\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Kelly:It's so cool, just involving\\u00a0all the different avenues of\\u00a0their culture.I mean, we have heard dance\\u00a0music, can-can, Lady Gaga.\", \"from\": 4375, \"to\": 4507, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 4497, \"end\": 4506, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Lady_Gaga\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Lady Gaga\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Lady_Gaga\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Lady_Gaga\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"I think we have heard everything.\", \"from\": 4508, \"to\": 4541, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Hard, heavy metal, opera.\", \"from\": 4542, \"to\": 4567, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Michael: It's hard enough to pull off\\u00a0in a stadium, but in the rain,\\u00a0especially, it has not rained in a summer Olympic opening ceremony since Helsinki in 1952.\", \"from\": 4569, \"to\": 4728, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 4711, \"end\": 4719, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Helsinki\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 1.1110993048469147e-14, \"text\": \"Helsinki\", \"types\": [\"Q515\", \"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Helsinki\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Helsinki\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"So, now Paris in 2024.\", \"from\": 4729, \"to\": 4751, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 4737, \"end\": 4742, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 3.479270854497296e-23, \"text\": \"Paris\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Peyton: It's me.\", \"from\": 4753, \"to\": 4769, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"It's my fault.\", \"from\": 4770, \"to\": 4784, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"I bring the rain.\", \"from\": 4785, \"to\": 4802, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"X users also noteda naked, blue man being served on a platter at the supper, and a person whoappears to be a transgender woman with a beard singing on the runway, all which were not aired on NBC's broadcasts.\", \"from\": 4804, \"to\": 5012, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 4995, \"end\": 4998, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/NBC\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 1.796923856340063e-13, \"text\": \"NBC\", \"types\": [\"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\", \"Q15265344\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/NBC\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/NBC\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"(They were apparently aired on European broadcasts.)\", \"from\": 5013, \"to\": 5065, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Kelly Clarkson gushed about the runway segment, stating, \\\"\\u2026that runway, Mike and I, we have been talking about this.\", \"from\": 5067, \"to\": 5183, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 5067, \"end\": 5081, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Kelly_Clarkson\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Kelly Clarkson\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Kelly_Clarkson\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Kelly_Clarkson\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Everyone is included at this table.\", \"from\": 5184, \"to\": 5219, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Like, every -- it does not matter who you are.\", \"from\": 5220, \"to\": 5266, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"They have -- represent all ages, all ethnicities, everything is represented on that runway, and I think that's so important that Paris did that.\", \"from\": 5267, \"to\": 5411, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 5396, \"end\": 5401, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 3.479270854497296e-23, \"text\": \"Paris\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"It's very cool.\\\"\", \"from\": 5412, \"to\": 5428, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Her co-host Mike Tirico agreed, saying, \\\"That's the spirit of this city, is not it?\\\"\", \"from\": 5430, \"to\": 5514, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 5442, \"end\": 5453, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Mike_Tirico\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Mike Tirico\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Mike_Tirico\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Mike_Tirico\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Kelly added it was \\\"inspiring.\\\"\", \"from\": 5515, \"to\": 5546, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 5515, \"end\": 5520, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Kelly_Osbourne\", \"score\": 0.9989247090021358, \"rank\": 0.0010764484935629388, \"text\": \"Kelly\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Kelly_Osbourne\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Kelly_Osbourne\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"No mention of the Christian mockery whatsoever.\", \"from\": 5547, \"to\": 5594, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 5565, \"end\": 5574, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Christianity\", \"score\": 0.9999997539917179, \"rank\": 2.460075966275219e-07, \"text\": \"Christian\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Christianity\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Christianity\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"More satanic imagery came during a dance that was supposed to be, \\\"representing the turmoil of the evils affecting the world,\\\" but the creators claimed the hell-like floor the dead bodies were dropping on was a\\u2026 volcano.\", \"from\": 5596, \"to\": 5816, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Michael: ...part of what has happened over the years at the Olympics is a call for peace around the world, and this dance is representing the turmoil of the evils affecting the world.\", \"from\": 5818, \"to\": 6001, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"These young people are dancing on a volcano.\", \"from\": 6002, \"to\": 6046, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"And this will morph into a more reflective moment of what has been a big part of this opening ceremony.\", \"from\": 6047, \"to\": 6150, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Kelly: Wow.\", \"from\": 6152, \"to\": 6163, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Mike: And after the celebratory mood thus far at the opening ceremony, a change of tune in the City of Light.\", \"from\": 6165, \"to\": 6274, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Wink, wink, it's just a volcano, folks!\", \"from\": 6276, \"to\": 6315, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Nothing to be concerned about here!\", \"from\": 6316, \"to\": 6351, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Towards the end of the ceremony, a mechanical horse \\\"gallops\\\" over the river with a rider wearing a cape with the Olympic symbol on it.\", \"from\": 6353, \"to\": 6488, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"The visionreminded many of The Book of Revelation in The Bible, which states in chapter 6, verse 8, \\\"I looked, and there before me was a pale horse!\", \"from\": 6489, \"to\": 6637, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Its rider was named Death, and Hades was following close behind him...\\\"  However, the creators claimed it was just representative of \\\"The Olympic Spirit\\\":  Michael: Translated to solidarity, a call to the world.\", \"from\": 6638, \"to\": 6849, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"If you recognize that bridge, that's Pont de Austerlitz where the parade and flotilla of boats down the Seine started.\", \"from\": 6850, \"to\": 6968, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 6895, \"end\": 6905, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Battle_of_Austerlitz\", \"score\": 0.999996671664203, \"rank\": 3.3283056638785416e-06, \"text\": \"Austerlitz\", \"types\": [\"Q1656682\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Battle_of_Austerlitz\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Battle_of_Austerlitz\"}, {\"begin\": 6954, \"end\": 6959, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Seine\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 4.650926879912855e-24, \"text\": \"Seine\", \"types\": [\"Q47521\", \"Q4022\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Seine\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Seine\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"3.7 miles and a few hours ago.And we have a rider on horse galloping on the Seine, which the creators tell us is a representation of the Olympic spirit carrying the Olympic flag.\", \"from\": 6969, \"to\": 7147, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 7045, \"end\": 7050, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Seine\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 4.650926879912855e-24, \"text\": \"Seine\", \"types\": [\"Q47521\", \"Q4022\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Seine\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Seine\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"As the horse rides under each bridge, the bridges light up with what appear to be angel wings.\", \"from\": 7149, \"to\": 7243, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"But, continuing their plausible deniability tactic, the creators claimed they were the wings of a dove.\", \"from\": 7244, \"to\": 7347, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"If anyone might have dismissed the mechanical horse being representative of Revelation because it wasn't technically white or pale, a real, white horse ends up taking over on land, at which point the Eiffel Tower lights up with another pair of wings.\", \"from\": 7349, \"to\": 7599, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"The wings appear to be coming from the back of the rider.\", \"from\": 7600, \"to\": 7657, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"But, sure, yeah.\", \"from\": 7658, \"to\": 7674, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"They are just wings of a dove.\", \"from\": 7675, \"to\": 7705, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"#eyeroll  Kelly: All right.\", \"from\": 7706, \"to\": 7733, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 7716, \"end\": 7721, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Kelly_Osbourne\", \"score\": 0.9989247090021358, \"rank\": 0.0010764484935629388, \"text\": \"Kelly\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Kelly_Osbourne\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Kelly_Osbourne\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Michael: So, here in Paris, the horse began its journey with the Olympic flag where the parade started 3.7 miles ago.\", \"from\": 7735, \"to\": 7852, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 7756, \"end\": 7761, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 3.479270854497296e-23, \"text\": \"Paris\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"It has now made its way not only on land but into the Trocadero Stadium to be joined by the flags of the nations competing in these games.\", \"from\": 7853, \"to\": 7991, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"As of this writing, #BoycottOlympics,#BoycottTheOlympics, and#BoycottParis2024were trending on X, with many people outraged by the shocking and offensive displays.\", \"from\": 7993, \"to\": 8156, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"One citizen of France even apologized to the world on behalf of her country:  The opening ceremony of the Olympics is not even hiding the satanic rituals anymore.There is no longer anything hidden in plain sight.These are the demonic dark forces of Satan who want to eclipse the light.You can already see:- Skulls- Motifs of death- Satanic red\\u2026pic.twitter.com/0C0zsfWd1X  If you still watch the Olympics after that disgusting display of anti-Christian, pedo, satanic filth in their opening ceremony - you are a part of the problem.If you can not even take a stand against that trash, what do you even stand for?\", \"from\": 8157, \"to\": 8768, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 8172, \"end\": 8178, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\", \"score\": 0.9999726700613193, \"rank\": 2.2411906689668545e-05, \"text\": \"France\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\"}, {\"begin\": 8406, \"end\": 8411, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Satan\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 1.6136403186531231e-28, \"text\": \"Satan\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Satan\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Satan\"}, {\"begin\": 8489, \"end\": 8496, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Satanism\", \"score\": 0.9999999998535714, \"rank\": 1.461501944966382e-10, \"text\": \"Satanic\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Satanism\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Satanism\"}, {\"begin\": 8594, \"end\": 8608, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Antichrist\", \"score\": 0.9999989871444668, \"rank\": 1.0128567514101717e-06, \"text\": \"anti-Christian\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Antichrist\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Antichrist\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"As a sincerely patriotic French girl, I disolidarise myself from this freakshow and apologize to you, world.#Paris2024pic.twitter.com/KXr55NdACW  #BoycottTheOlympicspic.twitter.com/N0BxQsATfm  This absolutely sick and offensive and crude display of anti-Christ blasphemy and heresy.Your message is loud and clear, you hate Jesus and us as his disciples.I count it all joy, and we will not forget.#boycotttheolympicshttps://t.co/TSsPSA3Mkv  Donor Privacy Policy  The mission of the Media Research Center is to document and combat the falsehoods and censorship of the news media, entertainment media and Big Tech in order to defend and preserve America's founding principles and Judeo-Christian values.\", \"from\": 8770, \"to\": 9470, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 8795, \"end\": 8801, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_language\", \"score\": 0.999986758778859, \"rank\": 1.0434054994948781e-05, \"text\": \"French\", \"types\": [\"Q315\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_language\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resour